   "status": "PREVIEW — the GAME wing of the O'Neill cylinder modelling package (main site; structure=rind, thermodynamics=tide, ecosystem=biome). Collaborative design space for 'the infinite game': a canvas glyph-world stitched from an endless deterministic ship engine (js/ship.js) where each place is a com.minomobi.hoop.place record anchoring a com.minomobi.hoop.message thread. Static Worker (ASSETS) + HoopRoom presence DO (live positions over WebSockets), no D1. Auth via shared workers/auth (origin allowlisted, hoop.place/hoop.message added to scope.ts). The structural half (cylinder/foam/solver) split out to the `rind` surface. VERSIONED SURFACES: v100 is the stable playable-nave snapshot; v103 is the frozen NPC-reform test surface (playable end-to-end: deck-aware keeper placement, rind-guide relocation, direction-aware waypoints, anchor briefings for the two setter-less gates); v104 (frozen prior) is the FUNGIBLE-KEEPER pass — a gate can be satisfied by ANY of several room bundles (gateSettersMulti), the ◇ points at the nearest PLACED satisfier (unifying the main quest with the side-thread seek model), and /quests shows the per-gate satisfier count so hoopy can verify his diversity draw. v105 (frozen prior) is the SEEDED-QUEST-SPINE pass — gate keepers are CAST from the 168-room-bundle pool per world seed (story/weave.js: every seed a different, provably progressable set of quest NPCs), all wards open after Olo's turn-in, and Factor Solen's tier closes on a procedural murder mystery (tide/case merged with room bundles: keeper-only cast, clues as spliced dialogue, a real accusation to the case-giver); /quests gains a seed roller + sweep prover. v106 (dev, current) is the UPPER-RIND EVERYTHING-FACTORY pass — deck 1 replaced by the ring-weave pocket world (rind/upperrind brought into the game): six white-collar ops threads × eight production threads (two of them ring loops touching all twelve), every crossing a zero-grade antechamber (no ladders), weave-aware waypoints that route between threads with minimal crossings, NPC keepers seated in the white threads, the nave lift at the top nexus and the lower rind off the bottom nexus.",
